The paper deals with the problem of visual monitoring using an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV), which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for determining visibility regions and monitoring multiple points of interest, which suggests the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The development of a constant-factor approximation algorithm and an ILP formulation for solving the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) and Generalized Traveling Salesman Problem (GTSP) respectively, indicates the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.GR) techniques. Finally, the comparative evaluation of solutions computed using different tools and parameters suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
